 * Shortcode: [dinoco_admin_transfer]
 * Description: ระบบย้ายเจ้าของสินค้าแบบ Force Transfer (Admin Override)
 * Version: V.31.5 (2026-05-14) — Sprint 20 HIGH-2: fire `dinoco/claim/
 *   owner_transferred` action post-COMMIT so Claim Payment LIFF V.0.8 +
 *   future subscribers can invalidate per-user transients. Hook fires after
 *   sn_pool atomic flip succeeds; non-blocking, non-failing.
 * Version: V.31.4 (2026-05-12) — R11 BLOCKER-1: 1 wrong-signature
 *   obs_capture( Throwable, ... ) call renamed to obs_capture_exception().
 * Version: V.31.3 (2026-05-07) — R4 BLOCKER #3 (fullstack #1):
 *   GET_LOCK timeout fallback 5s → 15s (matches REST API V.0.31 constant
 *   bump). Tech-lead R4 verdict: "concurrent activate vs admin swap race —
 *   bump 15s + idempotency TTL > timeout × 3." When REST API V.0.31 synced,
 *   `DINOCO_SN_LOCK_TIMEOUT` constant resolves to 15s automatically; fallback
 *   literal updated 5 → 15 so behavior is consistent during partial-sync
 *   windows. Doc comment "GET_LOCK(dnc_sn_{sn}, 5s)" → "15s" updated.
 * Version: V.31.2 (2026-05-07) — R3 CRIT-3 + F-NEW-1 — fire
 *   `dinoco_sn_pool_status_changed` post-COMMIT (was missing) +
 *   `dinoco_sn_pool_status_changed_for_user` for Member Dashboard subscriber.
 *   Use canonical helper dinoco_sn_lock_name() + DINOCO_SN_LOCK_TIMEOUT
 *   constant when REST API V.0.29 synced; fallback to inline literal
 *   otherwise. Both old + new owner receive for_user notifications so
 *   prior owner's dashboard refreshes too (transferred-out plate disappears).
 * Version: V.31.1 (2026-05-07) — C1 FIX: unified lock key 'dnc_sn_{md5}' to
 *   serialize properly with Activation + Service Center claim hooks. Without
 *   this fix, transfer + claim on same SN concurrently could interleave →
 *   prev_status corruption + state machine reject downstream ops.
 * Version: V.31.0 (2026-05-05) — Phase 2 W6.6 sn_pool integration + nonce hardening.
 *   • NEW dinoco_sn_transfer_owner_by_sn($sn, $old_owner, $new_owner) helper —
 *     atomic warranty owner transfer in wp_dinoco_sn_pool. SELECT FOR UPDATE +
 *     GET_LOCK + START TRANSACTION + try/catch ROLLBACK + finally RELEASE_LOCK.
 *     status flips registered → transferred (intermediate) → registered with new
 *     owner in same atomic transaction. Audit row written via dinoco_sn_audit_log
 *     (defensive function_exists guard). Boss decision Q16: Customer transfer =
 *     ใช้เพลทเดิม (no new plate issued — same physical SN, different owner).
 *   • NEW pre-flight guard before transfer: SELECT plate by sn → if status in
 *     [claimed, voided, recalled, replaced] → reject with localized message; if
 *     status = stolen → reject + alert บอส LINE. Defensive: missing sn_pool table
 *     or missing row (legacy SN before Phase 1 W2) → graceful no-op fall-through
 *     to legacy ACF-only logic, returns true.
 *   • Phase 1 audit BUG-S2 — nonce action consistency hardening. wp_create_nonce
 *     and wp_verify_nonce both use the action 'dinoco_admin_action'. Verified
 *     identical action name across emit (line ~158) and check (line ~53) sites.
